# Git & PR Hygiene

## What lands in a change

- **One concern** per PR (e.g. “Phase 7 schedule publish”, not “publish + redesign + random refactor”).
- Commit message = **why** (conventional `feat:` / `fix:` / `chore:` welcome).
- Schema change ⇒ Prisma migration files in the **same** change set.
- Meaningful app work ⇒ update `docs/Memory.md` in the same effort (checkboxes + session log).
- Stay inside active-phase scope unless Memory logs an override.

## Never commit

`.env`, secrets, DB dumps, huge binaries/media, `node_modules`.

## CI

Do not bypass lint / typecheck / unit tests to merge. Do not disable failing critical tests to “go green”.

## Author checklist

- [ ] Phase-scoped  
- [ ] No secrets  
- [ ] Migration if schema touched  
- [ ] New endpoints: Zod + AuthZ + ownership  
- [ ] Money/stock paths: transaction + idempotent where required  
- [ ] Regression/check for critical mutation when non-trivial  
- [ ] Memory updated  

## Refuse unless user explicitly accepts risk

Force-push to `main`/`master` · `--no-verify` · shipping with auth/validation removed “temporarily”.
